Octal and hexadecimal literalsOctalis base 8 -- that is, the only digits available are: 0, 1, 2, 3, 4, 5, 6, and 7. In Octal, we count like this: 0, 1, 2, 3, 4, 5, 6, 7, 10, 11, 12, … (note: no 8 and 9, so we skip from 7 to 10).Decimal01234567891011Octal0123456710111213To use an octal literal, prefix your literal with a 0 (zero):#include <iostream>

